1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:01,958
This used to be a small garden

2
00:00:02,458 --> 00:00:04,375
On days like these and at this time

3
00:00:04,667 --> 00:00:08,542
Especially when we came for Mass on Friday

4
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:11,458
We sat here and the weather was nice, you know spring weather is beautiful

5
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,000
Those were beautiful days in this place

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,583
God willing they will return

7
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,208
And we will restore the church to what it was

8
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:23,333
And their families will come back, how I wish they would return

9
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:26,292
I am the only one who came back here. May they return

10
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:29,167
Mosul is good now, God willing

11
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:33,792
Interviewer: Ari, what message do you give to the families who left?

12
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:36,833
Witness: Those who left Iraq, it is hard for them to return

13
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:40,500
But those still inside Iraq, let them come back to Mosul

14
00:00:40,958 --> 00:00:44,542
Their houses are still there, and the streets are fine

15
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:46,167
Mosul now is good and safe

16
00:00:47,042 --> 00:00:48,458
Like the other provinces

17
00:00:48,542 --> 00:00:50,375
Like the region, there is safety here

18
00:00:50,458 --> 00:00:51,458
Let them return

19
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:55,250
So we can see Mosul full of life, and beautiful

20
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,930
God willing they will return
